HEADWORD: Meteorometer
<hw>Me`te*or*om"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Meteor</ets> + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <def>An apparatus
which transmits automatically to a central station atmospheric
conditions as marked by the anemometer, barometer, thermometer,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

